cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Mobile AdHoc Networks (MANETs) and their implementation on smartphones. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also likely as the paper discusses the creation of a network of smartphones, which can be considered as a multi-agent system. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with the creation of a distributed network of smartphones. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the performance evaluation of the MANET and its impact on battery discharge rate, which can be considered as a control problem. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper briefly discusses the security implications of using ad-hoc smartphone networks.
